Ian M. Cook's Biography



Mr. Cook has been President and Chief Executive Officer of Colgate since July 2007 and Chairman of the Board since January 2009. Mr. Cook began his career at Colgate in 1976 and progressed through a series of senior marketing and management roles around the world. He was appointed Chief Operating Officer in 2004, with responsibility for operations in North America, Europe, Central Europe, Asia and Africa, and, in 2005, he was promoted to President and Chief Operating Officer, responsible for all Colgate operations worldwide.     Skills and Qualifications:     Business Operations-Extensive operational leadership experience through service as P ...
(Read More)

			Mr. Cook has been President and Chief Executive Officer of Colgate since July 2007 and Chairman of the Board since January 2009. Mr. Cook began his career at Colgate in 1976 and progressed through a series of senior marketing and management roles around the world. He was appointed Chief Operating Officer in 2004, with responsibility for operations in North America, Europe, Central Europe, Asia and Africa, and, in 2005, he was promoted to President and Chief Operating Officer, responsible for all Colgate operations worldwide.     Skills and Qualifications:     Business Operations-Extensive operational leadership experience through service as President and CEO and Chief Operating Officer of Colgate and strong knowledge of business finance and financial statements through oversight of operating budgets and financial statements at Colgate.     Industry-In-depth knowledge of consumer products industry and Colgate's business through over 40-year career at Colgate.     International-Experience managing Colgate's international operations and living and working in a number of foreign countries. Native of Great Britain.     Corporate Governance-Experience serving as a director of another U.S. public company.
		
Source: Colgate-Palmolive Company on 03/29/2017
		
	

 






