Ian M. Cook - Wikipedia





















 






Ian M. Cook

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search



Ian M. Cook


Nationality
British


Alma mater
London Guildhall University


Occupation
President, Chairman & CEO at
Colgate-Palmolive (2009–)


Salary
US$ 19,230,000 (2014)


Predecessor
Reuben Mark


Board member of
Pepsico, Colgate-Palmolive


Ian M. Cook is a British businessman.[1][2][3] He serves as the Chairman, President and Chief Executive Officer of Colgate-Palmolive.[4][5]
Biography[edit]
Ian M. Cook was born in Great Britain.[1] He graduated from London Guildhall University, now known as London Metropolitan University.[2] On 7 December 2015 he was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Business Administration.
He joined Colgate-Palmolive in the United Kingdom in 1976.[1][2][3][4][5] From 2002 to 2005, he served as Executive Vice President.[2][3][5][6] In 2004, he was appointed Chief Operating Officer, with responsibility for operations in North America, Europe, Central Europe, Asia and Africa.[1][2][3][4][5][6] In 2005, he became President and continued to serve as COO.[1][2][3][4][5] He was elected President, Chief Executive Officer and joined the Board of Directors in 2007.[1][2][3][4][5] In 2009, he became Chairman of the Board of Directors, and continued on as President and CEO.[1][2][3][4][5]
He has sat on the Board of Directors of Pepsico since March 14, 2008.[2][5] He is also a Director of Catalyst.[2][7] He sits on the Board of Directors of the Consumer Goods Forum.[8]
In 2011, he earned over US$14 million.[1]
